id: AIC-NAV-001-PY
type: component
owner: developer
extends:
  business: AIC-NAV-001
  language: aic-python-guidelines

component: NavigateCommand
file: python/navigate/NavigateCommand/navigate_command.py

implementation:
  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I1
    intent: |
      Entry point is a Click command named navigate().
      Accepts:
        --query: str     ← required, natural language task description
        --copy: bool     ← optional, copy output to clipboard
        --file: bool     ← optional, write output to .aic/context/
      All output deterministic — zero LLM calls.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I2
    intent: |
      Phase 1 — Query parsing (deterministic).
      Extract component name by matching query words against
      known component names found in /business folder.
      Extract language by matching query words against
      known language folders in project root.
      Extract action type from keywords:
        fix, create, migrate, explain, audit, update, add, remove
      If component ambiguous — list all business folder names
      and ask developer to clarify. Do not guess.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I3
    intent: |
      Phase 2 — File traversal (deterministic).
      Always read project.intent first — always in scope.
      If component matched — read business/<Component>/module.intent.
      If language matched — read <language>/<language>.intent or language.intent.
      If component + language matched — read
        <language>/<Component>/<Component>.intent.
      If component not matched — list business folder names only.
      Do not read sibling components — scope pollution prevention.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I4
    intent: |
      Phase 3 — Context assembly (deterministic).
      Concatenate all read files into one structured context block.
      Add header identifying what the context covers.
      Add footer with usage instruction.
      Format:

      ─────────────────────────────────────────
      AIC CONTEXT: <query>
      ─────────────────────────────────────────
      [PROJECT STANDARDS]
      <project.intent contents>
      ─────────────────────────────────────────
      [BUSINESS INTENT: <ComponentName>]
      <module.intent contents>
      ─────────────────────────────────────────
      [LANGUAGE GUIDELINES: <language>]
      <language.intent contents>
      ─────────────────────────────────────────
      [COMPONENT INTENT: <ComponentName> / <language>]
      <component.intent contents>
      ─────────────────────────────────────────
      Paste this context into your AI before describing your task.
      ─────────────────────────────────────────

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I5
    intent: |
      Phase 4 — Output (deterministic).
      Default: print assembled context to terminal.
      --copy flag: copy to clipboard using pyperclip if available.
        If pyperclip not installed print warning and fall back to terminal.
      --file flag: write to .aic/context/<query-slug>.txt
        query-slug is query string lowercased, spaces replaced with hyphens.
        Print file path after writing.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I6
    intent: |
      If no component matched in query:
        Print list of available components from /business folder.
        Print message: "No component matched your query."
        Print message: "Try: aic navigate --query '<ComponentName> your task'"
        Exit 0 — not an error, developer needs to refine query.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-PY-I7
    intent: |
      Always print a one-line summary before the context block:
        "Context assembled for: <matched components and language>"
      Always print file count:
        "Files included: X"
      This helps developer confirm the right files were picked.

platform-specific:
  - Clipboard copy uses pyperclip — optional dependency
  - Graceful fallback to terminal if pyperclip not installed
  - File slugification handles special characters safely

error-handling:
  - NotInitialisedError     → exit code 1
  - GitNotInitialisedError  → exit code 1
  - No match found          → exit code 0, list available components
  - File write error        → exit code 2, fall back to terminal output

implementation-note: |
  This command contains zero LLM calls.
  All four phases are fully deterministic.
  This is the bridge between developer query and AI context.
  Manual note for v1: developer pastes output into AI chat manually.
  MCP server wrapping this command is planned for v2.